The paper deals with dynamic maintenance of connectivity information in a graph, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of planar graphs is a specific constraint that is relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The algorithmic approach and analysis suggest that the paper may also be relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the practical application of the algorithm to handle edge deletions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to systems and control (cs.SI).
